Since dhergoloths are little more than dumb brutes, employers must use caution when instructing these fiends. They can handle simple orders that don’t take a lot of time to resolve. When given anything complex to do, they either forget what they’re told or don’t listen in the first place, and then bungle the task that was set for them.</text>
